               <head>Statuta antiqua et nova ordinis Carthusiensis. Germany, Mainz Charterhouse, s. xv<hi rend="superscript">in</hi>, A) (fols 1–161); B) (fols 162–207); C) (fols 208–225); D) (fols 226–271).</head>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>This description is abbreviated from Daniela Mairhofer, <title>Medieval Manuscripts from the Mainz Charterhouse in the Bodleian Library, Oxford: A Descriptive Catalogue</title> (Oxford, 2018), pp. 519–529. For purposes of scholarly citation, reference to the printed catalogue is requested.</p>
                  <p n="composite">Composite: A) (fols 1–161) || B) (fols 162–207) || C) (fols 208–225) || D) (fols 226–271)</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>parchment; bookmarks, made of red-coloured leather strips, glued to the outer margins of fols 73, 138, 163, 178, 199, 208 (damaged), 226 (lost) &amp; 263, to mark the beginning of item 2, parts 2 &amp; 3; item 3, including parts 2 &amp; 3, and items 4, 5 &amp; 7.</support>
                        <extent>i (17th-cent.) + 271 + i (17th-cent.) leaves</extent>
                        <foliation>i, 1–272, in modern (19th-cent) pencil.</foliation>
                        <collation>A) i 1+12 | ii–xiii 12 | xiv 8-4; B) xv 12 | xvi 8+1 | xvii 8 | xviii 10-2 | xix 10-1; C) xx 8 | xxi 10; D) xxii–xxiv 12 | xxv 10.</collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1639" notBefore="1637">
                        <p>Brown tanned calf over laminated pulpboard for Abp. Laud, 1637–1639.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
